                                "text": "maechler@stat.math.ethz.ch",
                                "unsafe": true
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ") changed:\n\n           What    |Removed                     |Added\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n             Status|UNCONFIRMED                 |CONFIRMED\n     Ever confirmed|0                           |1\n                 CC|                            |maechler@stat.math.ethz.ch\n\n--- Comment #3 from Martin Maechler ("
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "link",
                                "url": "mailto:maechler@stat.math.ethz.ch",
                                "text": "maechler@stat.math.ethz.ch",
                                "unsafe": true
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ") ---\nCan you confirm on __all__ platforms that "
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_preformatted",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "> identical(1 - 2^-53, 0.9999999999999999)\n[1] TRUE\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "If yes (which I guess with some confidence),\nthis will make alle the examples\/tests a bit more readable and \"typable\".\nPossibly even more importantly, I think we have on "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "all",
                                "style": {
                                    "italic": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " platforms nowadays"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_preformatted",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "> stopifnot(identical(2^-53, print(.Machine$double.neg.eps)))\n[1] 1.110223e-16\n> \n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "and one definition of e_ :=  the Machine's \"neg. epsilon\" is that it is the\nsmallest positive double prec number $\\epsilon$  fulfilling\n$$ 1 - \\epsilon \\neq 1 , $$\nsee"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_preformatted",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "> e2 <- 2^-(53:54); 1 - e2 < 1\n[1]  TRUE FALSE\n> e2 <- 2^-(52:53); 1 + e2 > 1\n[1]  TRUE FALSE\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "Note that the Wikipedia article shows that the definitions are more\nsophisticated, and the above is possible only a \"poor man\"'s version:\n"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "link",
                                "url": "https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Machine_epsilon"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\n\n(In reply to Deepayan Sarkar from comment #2)"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_quote",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ".............\n .............\n (I had initially thought it might have something to do with that\n  as both macOS and Windows uses clang)."
                            }
                        ],
                        "contains_padding": true
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "me, too...\nI think it would even more depend on the C library (libc) implementation\n(and runtime ?).\n\nNote that it "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "could",
                                "style": {
                                    "bold": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " be the bug in the respective C library, and python is\nworking around it (and we could too).\nI am marking this "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "CONFIRMED",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " now."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
