        "subtype": "bot_message",
        "text": "*[Bug 19091] as.numeric on macOS aarch64 rounds \"0.9999999999999999\" to 1.0 instead of the nearest IEEE 754 double*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=19091>\n\n--- Comment #5 from Deepayan Sarkar (<mailto:deepayan.sarkar@r-project.org|deepayan.sarkar@r-project.org>) ---\n(In reply to Martin Maechler from comment #3)\nNo &lt;==&gt; problematic platform, so this seems to be the underlying cause. Some\nkind of parsing error? The error happens with scan() as well.\n\nNote that the following program gives the \"correct\" output in all cases, even\non problematic platforms, so it is unlikely that Python is doing anything\nspecial.\n\n```\n#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;\n\nint main()\n{\n  double x;\n  printf(\"** %a **\\n\", (double) 0.9999999999999999);\n  sscanf(\"0.9999999999999999\", \"%lf\", &amp;x);\n  printf(\"** %a **\\n\", x);\n  return 0;\n}\n```",
